@page "/rating"

<ElliciumText TextStyle="TextStyle.H2" TagName="TagName.H1" class="rz-pt-8">
    Rating
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumText TextStyle="TextStyle.Subtitle1" TagName="TagName.P" class="rz-pb-4">
    Demonstration and configuration of the Ellicium Blazor <strong>Rating</strong> component.
</ElliciumText>

<ElliciumText Anchor="rating#get-set-value" TextStyle="TextStyle.H5" TagName="TagName.H2" class="rz-pt-8">
    Get and Set the value of Rating
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumText TextStyle="TextStyle.Body1" class="rz-mb-8">
    As all Ellicium Blazor input components the <strong>Rating</strong> has a Value property which gets and sets the value of the component. Use <code>@@bind-Value</code> to get the user input.
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumExample ComponentName="Rating" Example="RatingBindValue">
    <RatingBindValue />
</ElliciumExample>

<ElliciumText Anchor="rating#value-and-change-event" TextStyle="TextStyle.H5" TagName="TagName.H2" class="rz-pt-8">
    Get and Set the value of Rating using Value and Change event
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumText TextStyle="TextStyle.Body1" class="rz-mb-8">
    Value property can be used to set the value of the component and <code>Change</code> event to get the user input.
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumExample ComponentName="Rating" Example="RatingChangeEvent">
    <RatingChangeEvent />
</ElliciumExample>

<ElliciumText Anchor="rating#number-of-stars" TextStyle="TextStyle.H5" TagName="TagName.H2" class="rz-pt-8">
    Set number of stars
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumExample ComponentName="Rating" Example="RatingStars">
    <RatingStars />
</ElliciumExample>

<ElliciumText Anchor="rating#disabled-rating" TextStyle="TextStyle.H5" TagName="TagName.H2" class="rz-pt-8">
    Disabled Rating
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumExample ComponentName="Rating" Example="RatingDisabled">
    <RatingDisabled />
</ElliciumExample>

<ElliciumText  Anchor="rating#readonly-rating" TextStyle="TextStyle.H5" TagName="TagName.H2" class="rz-pt-8">
    Read-only Rating
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumExample ComponentName="Rating" Example="RatingReadOnly">
    <RatingReadOnly />
</ElliciumExample>

<ElliciumText Anchor="rating#keyboard-navigation" TextStyle="TextStyle.H5" TagName="TagName.H2" class="rz-pt-12">
    Keyboard Navigation
</ElliciumText>
<ElliciumText TextStyle="TextStyle.Body1" class="rz-mb-8">
    The following keys or key combinations provide a way for users to navigate and interact with Ellicium Blazor Rating component.
</ElliciumText>

<div class="rz-data-grid rz-datatable rz-datatable-scrollable" style="width: 100%;">
    <div class="rz-data-grid-data">
        <table class="rz-grid-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th style="padding: var(--rz-grid-cell-padding)">Press this key</th>
                    <th style="padding: var(--rz-grid-cell-padding)">To do this</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="rz-cell-data"><ElliciumBadge Text="Tab" /></span></td>
                    <td><span class="rz-cell-data">Navigate to a Rating item.</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="rz-cell-data"><ElliciumBadge Text="Shift" /> + <ElliciumBadge Text="Tab" /></span></td>
                    <td><span class="rz-cell-data">Navigate to a previous Rating item.</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="rz-cell-data"><ElliciumBadge Text="Space" /> or <ElliciumBadge Text="Enter" /></span></td>
                    <td><span class="rz-cell-data">Select a focused Rating item.</span></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>